 Worcestershire and the one in Warwickshire are named as ‘the dairy farm (Old English <i>wīc</i>) of Ceadel’. The other place in Worcestershire and the one in Lancashire are named as ‘Ceadda's dairy farm’. <i>Ceadda</i> was the name of a famous Anglo-Saxon bishop, Saint Chad. In Lancashire there was probably some confusion with another Lancashire name,   Chaddock  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Caddick","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Ancil.","Welsh: from an Anglicized form of the personal name <i>Cadog</i>, a pet form of <i>Cadfael</i> and the name of a famous saint, the first element of whose name is Welsh <i>cad</i> ‘battle’.","English: perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>caduc</i> ‘infirm, frail’ (Old French <i>caduc</i>). In Lancashire and Shropshire, <i>Cadwick</i> is a hypercorrect spelling, perhaps through association with the surname   Chadwick  ."]},{"name":"Chaddock","meanings":["English (Cheshire and Staffordshire): habitational name from Chaddock Hall in Tyldesley (Lancashire). There has probably been some confusion with another Lancashire name,   Chadwick  .","English (Devon): in southern England, probably a variant of <b>Shattock</b>, of uncertain origin."]},{"name":"Chadick","meanings":["English: variant of   Chadwick  ."]},{"name":"Chaddick","meanings":["English: variant of   Chadwick  ."]}]},{"name":"Sarah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah Chadwick was born in 1440, in Elland, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with John Bothomley. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1440–":"1440–Surnud","1440–Male":"1440–Surnud","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1539":"1539","Elland, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Elland, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1440–":"1440–Kuollut","1440–Male":"1440–Kuollut","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1440–Female":"1440–Kuollut","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1539":"1539","Elland, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Elland, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1440–":"1440–Décédée","1440–Male":"1440–Décédé","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1440–Female":"1440–Décédée","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1539":"1539","Elland, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Elland, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sarah Chadwick est née en 1440, à Elland, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec John Bothomley. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1440–":"1440–Verstorben","1440–Male":"1440–Verstorben","1462–1539":"1462–1539","1440–Female":"1440–Verstorben","1440":"1440","1462":"1462","1539":"1539","Elland, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Elland, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Sarah Chadwick wurde 1440 in Elland, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit John Bothomley mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb in ihrem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1440–":"1440–Desede","1440–Male":"1440–Desede","1462–1539":"